  "prompt": "How do you feel when people you hated appreciated you the most?",
  "response": "Feeling appreciated by someone you previously disliked can be complex. On one hand, it might evoke mixed emotions\u2014gratitude for the recognition but also confusion or resentment due to past feelings. It can challenge your perceptions and lead to introspection, prompting questions about personal growth and the capacity for change in relationships. Ultimately, it can be an opportunity to reevaluate feelings and perhaps find common ground or understanding. How do you feel about such situations?",
